The paper discusses interference management techniques in wireless networks, which falls under the category of computer networks and communications (cs.NI). The paper also discusses information theory concepts such as interference shaping and exploitation, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses multi-hop and multi-way network architectures, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses graphical illustrations, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses practical challenges associated with interference management, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
